The paper deals with the problem of catastrophic forgetting in deep neural networks, which is a common issue in the field of machine learning. The paper proposes a method called Few-shot Self Reminder (FSR) to overcome this problem. The paper uses popular benchmarks in computer vision and machine learning, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
